The paper deals with visual search systems and proposes a method for translating visual features across different systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed method involves the use of a Hybrid Auto-Encoder (HAE) and an Undirected Affinity Measurement (UAM), which are both machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of public datasets and the comparison of results with different types of features, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
